It is Christmas eve, Bobby is about to go on an adventure to celebrate Christmas with his grandfather. He thinks of the story he would tell his grandchildren. Mom had some Fiber Filled Holiday Biscuits. As they went on their car to Grandpa's house. The children are sick of the old music. Mom tells them to sing a new Christmas carol about Snow, Frosty the Snowman, the Knight before Christmas, the 3 Wise Men, the Round Young Virgin and Santa Claus and his 8 reindeer. As they reach Grandpa's house, Uncle Fred hungs the mistletoe. They put up the Christmas tree and added lots of lights, ornaments and tinsel, and Bobby hands the star to put on the tree. Bobby wishes for his Captain Squash Game Master. Uncle Fred overloads the socket and Bobby's family together has a wonderful Christmas dinner with turkey, mashed potatoes, peas and cranberries. Addison becomes the temporary obstetrician-gynecologist at the Oceanside Wellness Center in Los Angeles and treats a woman pregnant with a child whose paternity is disputed between three men. She also deals with the aftermath of the discovery that she cannot have children and is comforted by Pete Wilder who flirts with and eventually kisses her. The doctors offer her a position, but she denies after realizing that Seattle is where her life is. After Susan returns to the hospital with a severe chest pain, she is rushed into emergency surgery and ultimately dies. Thatcher is devastated by the news and blames Meredith for her death, who had actually been by her side all this time. Izzie finds difficulty in accepting that George is going to transfer because of her, but realizes that she can't deny her feelings towards him. Burke confronts his mother who claims that marrying Cristina is a mistake, but confesses that she trusts her son's judgement and is confident that he will make the right decision.

data: The Hand That Rocks the Cradle
Nancy and Arthur try babysitting to make extra money.
The Low Sodium, Adult Swim Only, Early Bird Special Vacation
Nancy is surprised to meet Polly when she visits her relatives in Miami.
Jessie cheats on an eye exam, which results in his having to get glasses. Meanwhile, Nancy and Charlie compete in a competition for the best sportsmen at school.

The kids watch a movie about the facts of life and have different reactions to it. Jessie misses most of the movie because of his mother, making him still not knowing from where the babies are coming from. Meanwhile, Polly opens the spoon hospital.
Nancy becomes Vinnie's girlfriend. Meanwhile, because of his aunt having a pool party, Arthur learns how to swim, but the teacher is Polly.

The kids compete in a Halloween costume contest. Jessie and Vinnie make a deal that they don't wear the Space Beast costume, but they end up breaking the deal. Nancy goes as Little Bo Peep and sees someone as a sheep, thinking that is Penny and not realizing that is actually Polly.
The kids compete at the school's fair to create the best booth.
A Visit to Nana and Pop-Pop's
Jessie visits his grandparents and he misses the spelling test. Meanwhile, back at school, Vinnie is sent to detention with Mr. Besser.
Nancy tries to convert her class to Feng Shui.

Nancy wants a haircut made by Simon from London, but she realizes that he makes the haircuts for the celebrities only. Nancy gets a haircut made by Nigel the cleaner and now she looks like a poodle. Meanwhile, Polly refuses to accept anything less than a perfect grade on a school paper.
Jessie skips his remedial math class. Meanwhile, Polly sells commemorative spoons.
Everyone wants to get even with Nancy when she takes over as writer, director and star of the school's play about Christmas. And they plan to do so on the night of the performance.

Mr. Besser is compelled to substitute for Miss Graves when she calls in sick. When she finds out that there was a mix-up, she decides to have a day off. Meanwhile, back at school, Vinnie does a report about Mr. Besser, the Liver Butcher. Vinnie fears that Mr. Besser will punish him when he finds out. Luckily, Vinnie wrote Mr. Besser's name wrong.
Polly runs for school president. When she wins the election, she decides to change all at school. Her plan backfires.
Nancy is thrilled when she breaks into a cool clique at school. Meanwhile, Jessie receives some nifty gifts for his good behavior.
Polly teaches Sanjay a dance called the Gazotski. Meanwhile, Miss Graves shares her lesson plans with Miss Bellanchof.
Nancy manages to obtain a hard-to-get press pass to see the hit group, The Sidewalk Boys.
Mr. Besser marries Vinnie's aunt. Meanwhile, Polly teaches a lesson on fire safety at school.

Arthur is nervous when he goes camping with the Squirrel Scouts because he's afraid to change his clothes in front of the others. Meanwhile, Nancy tries to spend time with Penny, but she gets stuck with Polly instead.

Miss Graves has trouble reaching a new student who's Miss Bellanchof's daughter, Melanie Bellanchof. Meanwhile, Nancy chooses to study India for an assignment and comes to believe that she had a previous life as a Hindu princess. Polly and Jordan argue about the assignments about Lithuania and China.
Don't Put Your Fingers in the Light Socket
Polly becomes Jessie's new babysitter, and he tries to keep that on a secret from the kids at school.

Nancy becomes the center of attention soon after she joins the garden club because of her knowledge about growing vegetables, but when she returns from a trip to Miami, she discovers that she's been forgotten.

Melanie is grounded, but her mom lifts it when Melanie starts to receive numerous party invitations. Meanwhile, Vinnie draws a revealing picture of Miss Graves called "Two Peaks", but he insists that it is only a drawing of two mountains.
Nancy suffers from asthma and she tries to keep that on a secret to the kids at school.

Jessie sings to the exchange program to copy from the exchange student. An exchange student, Lars Svenholm, from Outer Maledonia comes to Jessie. However, Lars turns out to be the same as Jessie. Jessie realizes that as a part of the exchange program, he'll have to leave to Outer Maledonia. Meanwhile, Polly opens the spoon school.

Fed up with that nobody from the class doesn't like her, Melanie decides to create a slam book and write something about someone. The girls begin to fight when they write bad things about themselves on the slam book.
Polly's goat, Schnitzy, died. Polly becomes very depressed. Nancy is forced to help Polly.

After watching Amber Amberset's new music video, Nancy and the girls begin to wear the rebellious clothes and the bells. The only one who isn't happy with all this is Mr. Besser. Meanwhile, to be more cool than Zack, Jessie and Vinnie decide to wear earrings. Jessie fears that he will get hurt during putting the earrings on his ears.

Miss Graves struggles with driving Nurse Pitts to school. In order to make sure that she doesn't find out that he didn't write his report about the planets, Jessie convinces Miss Graves to become forgetful because of Nurse Pitts. Meanwhile, Nancy is frightened by the tales about Billy Woofchuck who died when he answered the phone during a rainstorm.

Mr. Besser mistakes Jessie and Polly's scores of their IQ tests. Because of this, Jessie goes to the class for geniuses and Polly is forced to hang out with the dumb kids. The truth comes out when Jessie and Polly reveal their true school intelligences.

table-0076-987.caption: Season 1
data: Jessie gets the math book with the answers to the tests by mistake and it helps him becoming "smart". Because of this, he wins a prize at the math competition, but finds out that he has to answer the math questions in front of the whole school. Meanwhile, Nancy pretends that she has difficulty in listening, so she can sit up front with Penny, but instead, she is sent to see the school nurse.

Nancy returns from her vacation in Mexico with a charm bracelet and soon she becomes popular at school, but the bracelet vanishes and Nancy believes that it has been stolen. Meanwhile, Polly and Arthur are selected to be crossing guards, and Arthur immediately sets up a toll booth.

Jessie becomes an outcast after Freddie tells everyone that Jessie ate a piece of chewed gum that he found under his desk. Meanwhile, the kids try to watch a part of the documentary movie, "Chinook from the North", in which Chinook and his family stripped their clothes into nude.

Jessie is thrilled when he is teamed up with brains Freddie and Polly to present a committee report because he figures they'll do all of the work and he'll get the credit. Meanwhile, in order to match with the girls in the fashion, Nancy buys the fur hat, but it's too big and everyone laughs at her.

Jessie wants to be the funniest kid in class, so he memorizes a joke book of insults and his popularity makes him invited to Mary-Ellen's birthday party, but then he runs out of the insults and decides to use his own stuff - with disastrous consequences. Meanwhile, Arthur loses his ring and, in order to find it, he's hired to the Lost and Found office where Polly and Mr. Besser work. He manages to get Polly to get out of his way and keep all of the lost things to himself.

Nancy is excited when she is partnered with a new boy on a trip to a museum, only to learn that he doesn't speak any English. Arthur and Freddie try to find the vacancy toilet around the museum. Jessie tries to run away from his mother who joined the trip as a chaperone.

Jessie and Vinnie obtain a faculty phone list and use it to make prank phone calls until Mr. Besser finds out, but catches Vinnie only and makes him his helper for a week as punishment. When Jessie listens that Miss Graves wants to talk with his mother about something, he's convinced that she wants to tell his mother about phone pranks and fakes illness to stay at home and guard the phone. Meanwhile, Nancy pretends to be Polly's friend to join her and Penny in a weekend trip to the Lithuania Dance Festival.

Polly becomes a junior librarian and is determined to reclaim all of the library's overdue books, driving everyone crazy in the process. Arthur collects the books from his friends and opens his own library.

Arthur pretends to leave his lunch at home when he learns that the cafeteria workers give great free meals to kids who forget their lunches. Meanwhile, in order to get the revenge on Zack after he bullied her, Nancy tries to learn karate.

The kids get tired of Jessie's constant borrowing, so he finds a new mark in Freddie and even takes his homework. Meanwhile, Nancy tells the girls that she got a boyfriend named Jeremy, but Tillie suspects that he doesn't exist.
The Girl in the Plastic Bubble

Nancy is disappointed when she finds out that Penny pairs with Tillie at the sack race during the Sports Day. However, the illness problem attacks and Nancy tries to be well for the Sports Day. Meanwhile, Jessie is told by Miss Graves to take it easy in class after he bumps his nose and has to wear a bandage, but he takes advantage of the situation and wears it longer than he needs to.
Over the River and Through the Swamp

Arthur prepares to sing a solo at the school music festival until Polly barges in and turns his song into a duet. Meanwhile, Jessie cuts the pictures from the book to his report about the Mammals, but fears that someone will find out.

Freddie discovers that he and Polly are wearing the same cowboy shirt on picture day, so he tries to cover his shirt. Meanwhile, Jessie forgets about the biology test and tries to study until the test.
The Anti-Mucous Forming, Artery Clogging, Energy Zapping Diet

Penny begins to eat healthy food, so Nancy decides to eat healthy food too to match with her. Meanwhile, Freddie plans to take 10 friends to Monsterland, but Jessie and Vinnie want him to take fewer kids, so they can go on more rides.

Polly takes over reading the announcements over the school's public address system and soon starts to broadcast everyone's misdeeds. Meanwhile, Jessie stays at home for few weeks due to his ankle injury. At first, he wants to have fun, but Miss Graves decides to make him participate in the class with the help of the camera.

Jessie and Vinnie enter a science fair when they learn that the winners get to go to Space Camp, but they are caught cheating. Nancy and Penny do a project about the bugs for the science fair. Polly makes Freddie to help her with the project about the spoons.

Nancy is convinced that her bad luck is determined by the stars, so she turns to a Web-site astrology chart for guidance. Meanwhile, Freddie is accidentally sprayed by the water fountain, but everyone thinks that he was peeing his pants.

Jessie takes credit for a prank and is sent to Mr. Karl's class, where he encounters the school's toughest kids, who seem to never do any real work. Meanwhile, the classes prepare for the fire tests and the most of the class 402 sneak to the pool party at Arthur's aunt's house.

The girls try to avoid Polly, only to meet her in a park where she is riding a pony, which then makes them all (except Nancy) want to become friends with her. Meanwhile, Jessie fools Miss Graves that he sent his report about Tom Sawyer to his grandparents.

Jessie loses friends when he complains about missing a turn in a volleyball game and his mother gets involved. She treats him like a baby in front of his classmates and they begin to treat him like a baby too. Meanwhile, Nancy finds out that Jordan is very rich.

Jessie and Vinnie start using swear words at school after some tough boys curse at them for playing a babyish video game. When Polly catches them, they must stop swearing to don't let Mr. Besser and Miss Graves call their parents. Meanwhile, Nancy and the girls play many games to choose the first pair to play ping-pong.
Bing, Bing, Bing and a Shot

Polly updates the school's medical records and discovers that Jessie didn't have all of his required shots, thus making him get six of them. Meanwhile, the girl Squirrel Team delivers the cookies from door to door and the two best delivery girls will go to the Squirrel camp. Nancy tries to best deliver girl, so she can go to the camp with Penny.
